%[text] ## Preparation Task (pen and paper homework): Linearisation about hover
%[text] Derive the linearisation of the continuous time non-linear equations of motion about the hover equilibrium. Section 4.2 of the script describes the steps required and provides a brief review of linearisation. Specifically the pre-work exercise is to derive the linear system matrices given in equation (4.8) of the script, and come to class prepared to discuss points (i)–(iii) below. The derivation for linearising the equations of motion can be split up into 20 separate blocks, of which 13 blocks are identically zero due to there being no dependency of the expression on the variable of derivation, and 2 blocks are 3-by-3 identity matrices. Thus the derivation reduces to the following blocks:
